==English==
===Noun===
'''wire''' (uncountable and countable; plural: [[wires]])

# [[Cable]]; a [[thread]] or slender rod of [[metal]]; a metallic substance formed to an even thread by being passed between grooved rollers, or drawn through holes in a plate of steel.
# A [[telecommunication]] wire or cable; hence, an [[electric]] [[telegraph]]; a [[telegram]] 
# A hidden listening device on the person of an [[undercover]] operative for the purposes of obtaining incriminating spoken evidence.

